The three things to focus on are the client, server, and database
the client is the user
the server is a computer (hosting??)
the database is where you store data about your website
nested functions means a function within a function

/ is the home route like a home page.
we can create other paths by writing a word after the /
for example /contacts would be what takes the user to the contacts page.
You can also add a variable to the url by putting it in <>